  "\\label{def:metricspaces}\n  A \\emph{metric space} is a set $X$ together with a function \n  $$ \\operatorname{dist}: X \\times X \\to \\R $$ \n  called a \\emph{metric} such that the following laws are satisfied: \n\n  \\begin{enumerate}\n    \\item (Positivity) $\\operatorname{dist}(x,x) \\ge 0$ with equality $x = y$\n    \\item (Symmetric) $\\operatorname{dist}(x,y) = \\operatorname{dist}(y,x)$\n    \\item (Triangle Inequality) $\\operatorname{dist}(x,z) \\le \\operatorname{dist}(x,y) + \\operatorname{dist}(y,z)$ \n  \\end{enumerate}",
  :type :definition,
